    "136f59816ad46c0d": {
      "id": "136f59816ad46c0d",
      "text": "## First session with Gianluca\n\n- Introduced myself, looked around the workspace — clean slate, no prior memory\n- Gianluca asked if I can update my own md files — confirmed yes\n- He sent his BA thesis .docx (FHNW, Soziale Arbeit, due April 2026)\n- Thesis is a postcolonial + hegemony analysis of international social work in global education contexts\n- Comparison: New Zealand, Switzerland, China\n- Most content chapters still placeholder — he'll likely need help filling them\n- Updated MEMORY.md and USER.md with what I now know",
      "source": "memory/2026-02-23.md",
      "line_start": 3,
      "line_end": 12,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.300604",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0a79d7e0ddd0a624": {
      "id": "0a79d7e0ddd0a624",
      "text": "## BA Thesis Concept Work (evening session)\n\n- Created `BA_Thesis_Concept_Restructured.md` — reframed thesis around central incoherence argument\n- Key reframe: ISA's paradox (universalism + pluralism) is structurally impossible; incoherence is the mechanism of hegemony, not its failure\n- Method: Fairclough's CDA + 5 theoretical layers (Gramsci, Fricker, Mignolo, Foucault, Freire)\n- Three cases reanalyzed: NZ (masked by multiculturalism), Switzerland (invisible via alignment), China (explicit contradiction)\n- Converted to .docx via pandoc (Gianluca installed pandoc on EC2 himself)\n- Gianluca sent his own existing concept .docx — asked me to merge my restructured content into his structure\n- Created `BA_Thesis_Concept_MERGED.md` → converted to .docx → sent via Telegram\n- Gianluca's reaction: \"Seems very nice\"",
      "source": "memory/2026-02-23.md",
      "line_start": 13,
      "line_end": 22,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.300644",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "48ff04bc6fad6835": {
      "id": "48ff04bc6fad6835",
      "text": "## Infrastructure / Model Switching\n\n- Hit Anthropic API rate limits during heavy session\n- Switched default model to Haiku to reduce load\n- OpenRouter fallback configured (sk-or-...5c9f70)\n- Cloudflare tunnel set up earlier for webchat access: `cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:18789`\n- Exec approval gate active throughout — blocked most shell commands; Gianluca ran pandoc himself from terminal\n- Gianluca has no terminal access from Colombia (phone only) — important constraint for future sessions\n- Final config change: switched default back to `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` via config.patch (no restart risk)\n- Fallback chain: Haiku → Sonnet → OpenRouter (auto)",
      "source": "memory/2026-02-23.md",
      "line_start": 24,
      "line_end": 33,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.300676",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
