    "9d61d4355ef97e72": {
      "id": "9d61d4355ef97e72",
      "text": "---\nname: multi-model-orchestrator\ndescription: Orchestrates multiple AI models to complete complex tasks through task decomposition, model specialization, and result integration.\nuser-invocable: true\n---\n\n# Multi-Model Orchestrator\n\nCoordinates multiple AI models to accomplish complex tasks that no single model can handle alone.",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 10,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309247",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "db9ba57be10c5cae": {
      "id": "db9ba57be10c5cae",
      "text": "### 1. Task Analysis & Decomposition\n- Analyzes complex tasks to identify required capabilities\n- Breaks tasks into manageable subtasks\n- Determines optimal model for each subtask",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 13,
      "line_end": 17,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309261",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3438bf39b9daf1bd": {
      "id": "3438bf39b9daf1bd",
      "text": "### 2. Model Registry & Specialization\n- Maintains registry of available models with capabilities\n- Maps subtasks to appropriate models based on strengths\n- Handles model switching and fallback strategies",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 18,
      "line_end": 22,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309273",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "73ecb3bf7ec963c2": {
      "id": "73ecb3bf7ec963c2",
      "text": "### 3. Workflow Coordination\n- Manages sequential, parallel, and hierarchical workflows\n- Handles dependencies between subtasks\n- Monitors progress and handles failures",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 23,
      "line_end": 27,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309284",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "90e3c04a34b7d6b0": {
      "id": "90e3c04a34b7d6b0",
      "text": "### 4. Result Integration\n- Combines outputs from multiple models\n- Resolves conflicts between model outputs\n- Synthesizes final coherent result",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 28,
      "line_end": 32,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309294",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "18fe100c6571a83e": {
      "id": "18fe100c6571a83e",
      "text": "## Model Capabilities Mapping\n\n| Model Type | Strengths | Use Cases |\n|------------|-----------|-----------|\n| **Reasoning Models** | Logical analysis, step-by-step reasoning | Problem solving, planning, analysis |\n| **Creative Models** | Idea generation, writing, design | Content creation, brainstorming |\n| **Technical Models** | Coding, debugging, technical explanation | Programming, system design |\n| **Research Models** | Information synthesis, citation | Research, fact-checking |\n| **Specialist Models** | Domain-specific knowledge | Legal, medical, financial tasks |",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 33,
      "line_end": 42,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309318",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "66266b060d84311c": {
      "id": "66266b060d84311c",
      "text": "### Parallel Processing",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 50,
      "line_end": 54,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309327",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "77fe94bd37f3aa64": {
      "id": "77fe94bd37f3aa64",
      "text": "### Hierarchical Delegation",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 55,
      "line_end": 62,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309334",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "776ceea462e01aed": {
      "id": "776ceea462e01aed",
      "text": "## Integration with Existing Systems\n\n1. **OpenClaw Models**: Uses available OpenClaw model configurations\n2. **Perplexity-Inspired**: Integrates query analysis and source tracking\n3. **Async Agent Pattern**: Handles long-running multi-model workflows\n4. **Memory System**: Maintains context across model transitions",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 86,
      "line_end": 92,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309352",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0fefe3f573997b4e": {
      "id": "0fefe3f573997b4e",
      "text": "## Error Handling & Fallbacks\n\n- **Model failures**: Automatic fallback to alternative models\n- **Timeout management**: Configurable timeouts per model/subtask\n- **Quality validation**: Cross-checking between model outputs\n- **Progress tracking**: Resume interrupted workflows",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 93,
      "line_end": 99,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309367",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c2d7d1c683e6910c": {
      "id": "c2d7d1c683e6910c",
      "text": "### 1. Research Paper Writing\n- Model A: Research and gather sources\n- Model B: Outline structure\n- Model C: Write sections\n- Model D: Review and cite",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 131,
      "line_end": 136,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309382",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a9feb2a8f7c936af": {
      "id": "a9feb2a8f7c936af",
      "text": "### 2. Software Development\n- Model A: Requirements analysis\n- Model B: Architecture design\n- Model C: Code implementation\n- Model D: Testing and debugging",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 137,
      "line_end": 142,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309393",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "153c442ebe479df4": {
      "id": "153c442ebe479df4",
      "text": "### 3. Business Analysis\n- Model A: Market research\n- Model B: Financial analysis\n- Model C: Risk assessment\n- Model D: Report synthesis",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 143,
      "line_end": 148,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309403",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c351f10cf517c3bc": {
      "id": "c351f10cf517c3bc",
      "text": "## Performance Considerations\n\n- **Cost optimization**: Use cheaper models for simple subtasks\n- **Latency management**: Parallelize independent subtasks\n- **Token efficiency**: Minimize context passing between models\n- **Quality vs speed**: Configurable trade-offs",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 149,
      "line_end": 155,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309417",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ef19b41669d098ec": {
      "id": "ef19b41669d098ec",
      "text": "## Inspired By\n\nPerplexity Computer's approach to using multiple models for comprehensive task completion, combining specialized capabilities for optimal results.",
      "source": "skills/multi-model-orchestrator/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 156,
      "line_end": 158,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309427",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6cc9d13f8e63c2bb": {
      "id": "6cc9d13f8e63c2bb",
      "text": "---\nname: stats\nuser-invocable: true\ndescription: Show a compact system + session overview including disk, RAM, swap, thesis files, workspace size, sub-agent status, hardware info, and API/TPS metrics.\n---\n\n# Stats Skill\n\nWhen invoked via `/stats`, run the enhanced stats script and return a compact summary.",
      "source": "skills/stats/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 10,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309465",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6ec0c9152033cd00": {
      "id": "6ec0c9152033cd00",
      "text": "## Steps\n\n1. Run: `bash /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/stats.sh`\n2. Format the output as a clean, compact reply\n3. Append current model + context size from session_status if available",
      "source": "skills/stats/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 11,
      "line_end": 16,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309478",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7c40264fb5f11392": {
      "id": "7c40264fb5f11392",
      "text": "## Output Sections\n\nThe script outputs these sections:\n- **HARDWARE**: Host, kernel, CPU model, cores, RAM, swap, disk\n- **SYSTEM**: Uptime, load average\n- **GATEWAY**: Gateway status (bind, port, auth)\n- **MODEL & API**: Current model, reasoning enabled, TPS measurement\n- **OPENCLAW STATUS**: Version, Node.js, pending approvals, session count\n- **THESIS**: Latest thesis file, modification date, word count\n- **WORKSPACE**: Size, file count, skill count",
      "source": "skills/stats/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 17,
      "line_end": 26,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309499",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8ea55840490f0b27": {
      "id": "8ea55840490f0b27",
      "text": "## Output format\n\nReply in plain text, compact, no markdown tables. Group by section with a single blank line between sections.",
      "source": "skills/stats/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 28,
      "line_end": 30,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309510",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0c41a20aad85fc10": {
      "id": "0c41a20aad85fc10",
      "text": "---\nname: research\ndescription: \"Deep research skill - comprehensive information gathering and analysis using multi-model orchestration\"\ntrigger: \"research\"\n---\n\n# Research Skill",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 8,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309568",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "2fef38d2fb079c77": {
      "id": "2fef38d2fb079c77",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nA comprehensive research skill that triggers when you say \"research something\" or similar phrases. Uses multi-model orchestration for deep, thorough information gathering and analysis.",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 9,
      "line_end": 12,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309581",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "5c6c1a66301acd5e": {
      "id": "5c6c1a66301acd5e",
      "text": "## Trigger Phrases\n\nThe skill activates when messages contain:\n- \"research\" (as a verb: \"research X\", \"do research on Y\")\n- \"look into\"\n- \"investigate\"\n- \"find information about\"\n- \"analyze\" (when combined with research intent)\n- \"study\" (when research-focused)",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 13,
      "line_end": 22,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309596",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4eb2b978339cd9ff": {
      "id": "4eb2b978339cd9ff",
      "text": "### 1. Research Pipeline",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 25,
      "line_end": 29,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309603",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f0a095446c210a5d": {
      "id": "f0a095446c210a5d",
      "text": "### 2. Model Coordination\n- **Research Phase:** gemini-pro (research capability)\n- **Analysis Phase:** claude-sonnet (reasoning + analysis)\n- **Writing Phase:** gpt-4 (creativity + writing)\n- **Review Phase:** claude-sonnet (review)",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 30,
      "line_end": 35,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309616",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "34107a4a14358755": {
      "id": "34107a4a14358755",
      "text": "### 3. Information Sources\n1. **Web search** (when Brave API available)\n2. **Academic/scholarly sources**\n3. **Current news** (time-sensitive topics)\n4. **Official documentation**\n5. **Memory system** (past research)",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 36,
      "line_end": 42,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309629",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3d7e18788ea43843": {
      "id": "3d7e18788ea43843",
      "text": "### Research with Constraints",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 61,
      "line_end": 68,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309638",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fc15cec0f761ca32": {
      "id": "fc15cec0f761ca32",
      "text": "### Core Components\n\n1. **`research_skill.py`** - Main skill handler\n2. **`research_pipeline.py`** - Multi-stage research workflow\n3. **`query_analyzer.py`** - Parse research intent and scope\n4. **`source_tracker.py`** - Track information sources and citations",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 71,
      "line_end": 77,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309653",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "766843693c513267": {
      "id": "766843693c513267",
      "text": "### Integration Points\n\n- **Multi-Model Orchestrator** - Coordinates AI models for research\n- **Perplexity-Inspired Skill** - Query analysis and source citation\n- **Async Agent Pattern** - Long-running research tasks\n- **Memory System** - Store and retrieve research findings",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 78,
      "line_end": 84,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309668",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1fe2f858e8daa4b0": {
      "id": "1fe2f858e8daa4b0",
      "text": "## Research Methodology",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 85,
      "line_end": 86,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309674",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "664bcddf48e6bdb3": {
      "id": "664bcddf48e6bdb3",
      "text": "### 1. Scope Definition\n- Identify research question\n- Determine breadth vs. depth\n- Set time constraints (current vs. historical)\n- Define required sources",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 87,
      "line_end": 92,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309684",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f84c26aaa15571af": {
      "id": "f84c26aaa15571af",
      "text": "### 2. Information Gathering\n- Multi-source collection\n- Source credibility assessment\n- Time sensitivity consideration\n- Cross-verification",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 93,
      "line_end": 98,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309707",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "2a92d43aa06005ae": {
      "id": "2a92d43aa06005ae",
      "text": "### 3. Analysis & Synthesis\n- Pattern identification\n- Trend analysis\n- Comparative evaluation\n- Gap identification",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 99,
      "line_end": 104,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309717",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c3edc30eaa145336": {
      "id": "c3edc30eaa145336",
      "text": "### 4. Report Generation\n- Structured format\n- Source citations\n- Key findings summary\n- Recommendations/next steps",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 105,
      "line_end": 110,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309726",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "35a4203d1c593bf0": {
      "id": "35a4203d1c593bf0",
      "text": "### Standard Research Report",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 113,
      "line_end": 151,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309735",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6008043fb37d4906": {
      "id": "6008043fb37d4906",
      "text": "### Research Depth Levels\n1. **Quick** - Surface-level, 1-2 models, <5 minutes\n2. **Standard** - Comprehensive, 2-3 models, 5-15 minutes\n3. **Deep** - Thorough, 3+ models, 15-30+ minutes\n4. **Academic** - Scholarly, multiple sources, citations, peer-review style",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 154,
      "line_end": 159,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309750",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4de1ffcf5b8e2462": {
      "id": "4de1ffcf5b8e2462",
      "text": "### Source Priority\n1. **Academic** - Peer-reviewed journals, conferences\n2. **Official** - Government reports, organizational publications\n3. **News** - Current events, recent developments\n4. **Web** - General information, blogs, documentation",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 160,
      "line_end": 165,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309763",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4de76040a5f7f1cd": {
      "id": "4de76040a5f7f1cd",
      "text": "### Example 1: Technology Research",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 168,
      "line_end": 175,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309771",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "268d6872e5925fa5": {
      "id": "268d6872e5925fa5",
      "text": "### Example 2: Social Science Research",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 176,
      "line_end": 183,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309778",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4d5a20ba0c37b6d5": {
      "id": "4d5a20ba0c37b6d5",
      "text": "### Example 3: Current Events Research",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 184,
      "line_end": 191,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309784",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "83ae6312ac3221e5": {
      "id": "83ae6312ac3221e5",
      "text": "## Integration with Existing Workflow",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 192,
      "line_end": 193,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309790",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b6db7acc6432ccfd": {
      "id": "b6db7acc6432ccfd",
      "text": "### Heartbeat Integration\nResearch tasks can be scheduled via heartbeat for:\n- Daily research briefings\n- Weekly topic deep dives\n- Ongoing research projects",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 194,
      "line_end": 199,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309800",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f5dbd3a4e5c7e371": {
      "id": "f5dbd3a4e5c7e371",
      "text": "### Memory Integration\n- Store research findings in memory system\n- Create research topic embeddings\n- Enable semantic search across past research\n- Build knowledge graph of research topics",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 200,
      "line_end": 205,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309811",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "637bd8f0c09eaddd": {
      "id": "637bd8f0c09eaddd",
      "text": "### Project Integration\n- Link research to thesis projects\n- Track research progress\n- Organize findings by project\n- Generate literature reviews",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 206,
      "line_end": 211,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309822",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "32bbdc210cba0340": {
      "id": "32bbdc210cba0340",
      "text": "### Validation Methods\n1. **Cross-model verification** - Multiple models analyze same data\n2. **Source credibility scoring** - Rate sources by authority/recency\n3. **Consistency checking** - Ensure findings are internally consistent\n4. **Bias detection** - Identify potential biases in sources/analysis",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 214,
      "line_end": 219,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309837",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a344b378b91e54b4": {
      "id": "a344b378b91e54b4",
      "text": "### Confidence Scoring\n- **High (0.8-1.0)** - Multiple reliable sources, consistent findings\n- **Medium (0.5-0.8)** - Limited sources, some uncertainty\n- **Low (0.0-0.5)** - Inconclusive, needs more research",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 220,
      "line_end": 224,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309850",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "766def850fad31a9": {
      "id": "766def850fad31a9",
      "text": "### Current Constraints\n1. **Web search dependency** - Requires Brave API for external research\n2. **Model availability** - Limited to configured AI models\n3. **Time constraints** - Deep research requires significant time\n4. **Source access** - Some sources may be paywalled or restricted",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 227,
      "line_end": 232,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309865",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d4bbcedf6984806f": {
      "id": "d4bbcedf6984806f",
      "text": "### Mitigation Strategies\n- Use memory system for past research\n- Leverage multi-model analysis for depth\n- Implement progressive disclosure (quick → deep)\n- Cache research findings for similar queries",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 233,
      "line_end": 238,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309879",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f6cf4d3658339170": {
      "id": "f6cf4d3658339170",
      "text": "## Future Enhancements",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 239,
      "line_end": 240,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309885",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d7d03db4b61565f9": {
      "id": "d7d03db4b61565f9",
      "text": "### Planned Features\n1. **Automated literature review** - Academic paper analysis\n2. **Research topic tracking** - Monitor developments over time\n3. **Comparative research** - Side-by-side analysis of multiple topics\n4. **Visual research outputs** - Charts, graphs, timelines\n5. **Collaborative research** - Share findings, peer review",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 241,
      "line_end": 247,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309901",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "af0e3e1360ff34b0": {
      "id": "af0e3e1360ff34b0",
      "text": "### Integration Goals\n1. **Thesis research assistant** - Specialized for academic research\n2. **News monitoring** - Daily research briefings on selected topics\n3. **Knowledge base builder** - Automatically expand memory system\n4. **Research dashboard** - Track all research activities and findings",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 248,
      "line_end": 253,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309916",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4a630f1f9c3db781": {
      "id": "4a630f1f9c3db781",
      "text": "### Best Practices\n1. **Be specific** - Clear research questions yield better results\n2. **Set scope** - Define breadth/depth expectations\n3. **Consider time** - Recent vs. historical information needs\n4. **Review sources** - Always check source credibility",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 256,
      "line_end": 261,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309932",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "77d97fa2878a2eaa": {
      "id": "77d97fa2878a2eaa",
      "text": "### Common Use Cases\n- Academic research support\n- Market/competitor analysis\n- Technology evaluation\n- Policy research\n- Historical analysis\n- Current events monitoring",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 262,
      "line_end": 269,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309945",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "efe252dc6cdef716": {
      "id": "efe252dc6cdef716",
      "text": "### Basic Usage\nJust say \"research [topic]\" and the skill will automatically:\n1. Analyze your query\n2. Determine appropriate research depth\n3. Coordinate multiple AI models\n4. Return comprehensive findings",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 272,
      "line_end": 278,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309959",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ca896b24409767e3": {
      "id": "ca896b24409767e3",
      "text": "### Advanced Usage\nFor more control, specify:\n- \"deep research on [topic]\" - More thorough analysis\n- \"quick research on [topic]\" - Surface-level overview\n- \"academic research on [topic]\" - Scholarly focus\n- \"current research on [topic]\" - Recent developments only",
      "source": "skills/research/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 279,
      "line_end": 284,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.309973",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "90da01d136231b39": {
      "id": "90da01d136231b39",
      "text": "---\nname: audio-transcription\ndescription: \"Transcribe audio files to text using various methods. Use when: (1) User sends audio messages (OGG, MP3, WAV, etc.) that need transcription, (2) Processing voice notes or recordings, (3) Converting speech to text for documentation, (4) Handling audio files in workflows that require text input.\"\n---\n\n# Audio Transcription",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310036",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c7db964fc65bacd8": {
      "id": "c7db964fc65bacd8",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nThis skill provides methods for transcribing audio files to text. Since OpenClaw agents don't have built-in speech-to-text capabilities, this skill outlines approaches for handling audio files through external tools, APIs, or conversion workflows.",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310051",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4bf201abf59aac81": {
      "id": "4bf201abf59aac81",
      "text": "## Quick Start: Audio File Handling\n\nWhen you receive an audio file:\n\n1. **Identify the format:** Check file extension (.ogg, .mp3, .wav, .m4a, etc.)\n2. **Read metadata:** Use `read` tool on the audio file to see header information\n3. **Choose transcription method:** Based on available tools and file characteristics",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 12,
      "line_end": 19,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310067",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8db289fc4ed308b1": {
      "id": "8db289fc4ed308b1",
      "text": "## Available Transcription Methods",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 20,
      "line_end": 21,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310074",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "80ff44b38f60bc2c": {
      "id": "80ff44b38f60bc2c",
      "text": "### Method 1: API-Based Transcription (Recommended)\n\n**When to use:** When you have access to speech-to-text APIs (OpenAI Whisper, Google Cloud Speech-to-Text, etc.)\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Convert audio to compatible format if needed (WAV, MP3)\n2. Upload to API endpoint\n3. Process response and extract transcription\n\n**Example API call structure:**",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 22,
      "line_end": 42,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310092",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9991b87228df3fd8": {
      "id": "9991b87228df3fd8",
      "text": "### Method 2: Local Whisper Installation\n\n**When to use:** When you can install and run Whisper locally\n\n**Setup:**\n\n**Usage:**",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 44,
      "line_end": 61,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310104",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7c8053c39407a38b": {
      "id": "7c8053c39407a38b",
      "text": "### Method 3: Google Cloud Speech-to-Text\n\n**When to use:** When you have Google Cloud credentials\n\n**Setup:**\n\n**Configuration requires:**\n- Service account credentials\n- Project ID setup\n- API enablement",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 62,
      "line_end": 74,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310117",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "62eb42acc9eb5b29": {
      "id": "62eb42acc9eb5b29",
      "text": "### Method 4: FFmpeg + Basic Processing\n\n**When to use:** For simple audio conversion when transcription isn't available\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Convert to standard format\n2. Extract metadata\n3. Provide file details to user for manual processing",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 76,
      "line_end": 92,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310132",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "eca50a87820e8c18": {
      "id": "eca50a87820e8c18",
      "text": "## Common Audio Formats",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 93,
      "line_end": 94,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310138",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "08717ad36275f121": {
      "id": "08717ad36275f121",
      "text": "### OGG (Opus)\n- Common in Telegram voice messages\n- Container format with Opus audio codec\n- May need conversion for some APIs",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 95,
      "line_end": 99,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310147",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f37b58eb77c5498d": {
      "id": "f37b58eb77c5498d",
      "text": "### MP3\n- Widely supported\n- Most APIs accept MP3 directly",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 100,
      "line_end": 103,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310155",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "17b50283b035e478": {
      "id": "17b50283b035e478",
      "text": "### WAV\n- Uncompressed, high quality\n- Large file size\n- Universally compatible",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 104,
      "line_end": 108,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310162",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "812b8b3334554c91": {
      "id": "812b8b3334554c91",
      "text": "### M4A/AAC\n- Apple format\n- May need conversion",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 109,
      "line_end": 112,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310169",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "61ed47d4fb497292": {
      "id": "61ed47d4fb497292",
      "text": "## Workflow Decision Tree",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 113,
      "line_end": 126,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310177",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "474a569ecc4e8b32": {
      "id": "474a569ecc4e8b32",
      "text": "## Handling Telegram Audio Messages\n\nTelegram often sends OGG files with Opus codec. Typical path pattern:\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Read file header to confirm format\n2. Check if transcription is possible with available tools\n3. If not, inform user and suggest alternatives",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 127,
      "line_end": 138,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310191",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b3694331dc8f4be9": {
      "id": "b3694331dc8f4be9",
      "text": "## Scripts and Utilities",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 139,
      "line_end": 140,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310197",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "64206242d9681c7e": {
      "id": "64206242d9681c7e",
      "text": "### `scripts/transcribe_audio.py`\nMain transcription script that tries multiple methods in order:\n1. Check for local Whisper installation\n2. Fall back to API if configured\n3. Provide conversion options as last resort",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 141,
      "line_end": 146,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310209",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9c5c38ac458f9ffe": {
      "id": "9c5c38ac458f9ffe",
      "text": "### `scripts/convert_audio.py`\nAudio format conversion utility using FFmpeg.",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 147,
      "line_end": 149,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310217",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4c5868c87662a86c": {
      "id": "4c5868c87662a86c",
      "text": "### `scripts/audio_metadata.py`\nExtract and display audio file metadata.",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 150,
      "line_end": 152,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310225",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "68909f9b63159fb9": {
      "id": "68909f9b63159fb9",
      "text": "## References\n\nSee `references/audio_formats.md` for detailed format specifications and compatibility matrices.\n\nSee `references/api_setup.md` for API configuration guides (OpenAI, Google Cloud, etc.).",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 153,
      "line_end": 158,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310237",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a1748a942458ea79": {
      "id": "a1748a942458ea79",
      "text": "### Issue: \"No speech-to-text capability\"\n**Solution:** This is the default state. Use this skill to implement transcription through external tools.",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 161,
      "line_end": 163,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310249",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "288d7568c3a87f99": {
      "id": "288d7568c3a87f99",
      "text": "### Issue: Audio format not supported\n**Solution:** Convert to WAV or MP3 using FFmpeg:",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 164,
      "line_end": 169,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310257",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "225f4787150b9352": {
      "id": "225f4787150b9352",
      "text": "### Issue: Poor transcription quality\n**Solutions:**\n- Use larger Whisper models (medium, large)\n- Specify language parameter\n- Clean audio with noise reduction\n- Ensure proper sample rate (16kHz recommended)",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 170,
      "line_end": 176,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310269",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1904ed8416cc6c56": {
      "id": "1904ed8416cc6c56",
      "text": "### Issue: Large file size\n**Solution:** Compress or segment audio before processing.",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 177,
      "line_end": 179,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310277",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0dedb3562bf52f6a": {
      "id": "0dedb3562bf52f6a",
      "text": "## Integration with OpenClaw Workflow\n\nWhen you receive an audio file in OpenClaw:\n\n1. **Acknowledge receipt:** \"Received audio file, processing...\"\n2. **Attempt transcription:** Using available methods\n3. **Provide results or alternatives:**\n   - Success: Provide transcript\n   - Partial: Provide what you could extract + suggestions\n   - Failure: Explain limitations and suggest workarounds",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 180,
      "line_end": 189,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310296",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "11d269769afbe4b9": {
      "id": "11d269769afbe4b9",
      "text": "## Example User Interactions\n\n**User:** *sends audio file*\n**Assistant:** \"I received your audio message. Let me transcribe it for you...\"\n\n**User:** \"Can you transcribe this voice note?\"\n**Assistant:** \"I'll need to use speech-to-text tools. Let me check what's available...\"\n\n**User:** \"What did I say in the audio?\"\n**Assistant:** \"I can't transcribe audio directly, but I can help you set up transcription tools or convert the file for manual processing.\"",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 191,
      "line_end": 200,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310317",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "33ccf2be57854ccb": {
      "id": "33ccf2be57854ccb",
      "text": "---\nname: external-terminal-access\ndescription: \"Access external terminals and web interfaces through links and shared sessions\"\n---\n\n# External Terminal Access Skill",
      "source": "skills/external-terminal-access/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310370",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0a8280a658e36ce1": {
      "id": "0a8280a658e36ce1",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nThis skill enables access to external terminals, web interfaces, and shared sessions through various protocols and tools.",
      "source": "skills/external-terminal-access/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310380",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "808f25e03b6ef068": {
      "id": "808f25e03b6ef068",
      "text": "## Current Capabilities",
      "source": "skills/external-terminal-access/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 12,
      "line_end": 13,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310386",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e61e6c50db92f97c": {
      "id": "e61e6c50db92f97c",
      "text": "### 1. SSH Terminal Access\n- **Port:** 22 (already open)\n- **User:** ubuntu\n- **Host:** 172.31.14.61\n- **Status:** Accessible via Termius, OpenSSH, etc.",
      "source": "skills/external-terminal-access/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 14,
      "line_end": 19,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310397",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9fc74a8c1a1f8a79": {
      "id": "9fc74a8c1a1f8a79",
      "text": "### 2. Claude Code Terminal\n- **Command:** `claude`\n- **Status:** Installed and configured\n- **Workspace:** `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace` (trusted)\n- **Access:** Direct terminal interaction",
      "source": "skills/external-terminal-access/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 20,
      "line_end": 25,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310409",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "5d1a481e8e699f46": {
      "id": "5d1a481e8e699f46",
      "text": "### 3. Web Interfaces\n- **OpenClaw Control UI:** `http://172.31.14.61:18789/`\n- **Memory Visualization:** `http://172.31.14.61:5000/` (if running)\n- **Browser Control:** Brave on port 9223 (CDP)",
      "source": "skills/external-terminal-access/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 26,
      "line_end": 30,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.310422",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
