    "b79a645b836e2924": {
      "id": "b79a645b836e2924",
      "text": "## Monitoring and Alerting",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 246,
      "line_end": 247,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311224",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7d240aee2501d88e": {
      "id": "7d240aee2501d88e",
      "text": "### 1. Idempotent Scripts\nScripts should be safe to run multiple times:",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 291,
      "line_end": 300,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311238",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8dc5fe3469ead73a": {
      "id": "8dc5fe3469ead73a",
      "text": "### 2. Proper Error Handling",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 301,
      "line_end": 313,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311245",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "cd06fc667360d9d3": {
      "id": "cd06fc667360d9d3",
      "text": "### 3. Resource Management",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 314,
      "line_end": 323,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311252",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6459c8f3f6bc9f2a": {
      "id": "6459c8f3f6bc9f2a",
      "text": "## Automation Scripts",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 339,
      "line_end": 340,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311259",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ac585e3635f88aec": {
      "id": "ac585e3635f88aec",
      "text": "### `scripts/service_setup.py`\nSet up new services with proper configuration:\n- Create systemd service files\n- Configure cron jobs\n- Set up logging\n- Add monitoring",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 341,
      "line_end": 347,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311270",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4a6b83fe5e0cb7b5": {
      "id": "4a6b83fe5e0cb7b5",
      "text": "### `scripts/cron_deploy.py`\nDeploy and manage cron jobs:\n- Validate cron syntax\n- Backup existing jobs\n- Deploy new jobs\n- Test execution",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 348,
      "line_end": 354,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311280",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0442e46455a738c3": {
      "id": "0442e46455a738c3",
      "text": "### `scripts/process_manager.py`\nManage background processes:\n- Start/stop processes\n- Monitor health\n- Restart on failure\n- Clean up resources",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 355,
      "line_end": 361,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311290",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c20868095e8e87e7": {
      "id": "c20868095e8e87e7",
      "text": "## References\n\n- `references/cron_reference.md`: Complete cron syntax reference\n- `references/systemd_guide.md`: Systemd service configuration\n- `references/process_management.md`: Process management techniques\n- `references/security_best_practices.md`: Security considerations for services",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 362,
      "line_end": 368,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311305",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "31a95fb73056037a": {
      "id": "31a95fb73056037a",
      "text": "## Integration with System Diagnostics\n\nCombine with system-diagnostics skill for comprehensive management:\n1. **Monitor** with system-diagnostics\n2. **Manage** with service-management\n3. **Fix** issues as they arise\n4. **Prevent** future problems",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 369,
      "line_end": 376,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311319",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ddac11b92756232c": {
      "id": "ddac11b92756232c",
      "text": "## Emergency Procedures",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 377,
      "line_end": 378,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311325",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a4e7c31ee69064de": {
      "id": "a4e7c31ee69064de",
      "text": "### Service Won't Start\n1. Check logs: `journalctl -u service-name`\n2. Test manually: Run command directly\n3. Check dependencies: Ports, files, permissions\n4. Simplify: Remove non-essential configuration",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 379,
      "line_end": 384,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311337",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "73e5d581ec51945d": {
      "id": "73e5d581ec51945d",
      "text": "### Cron Job Flooding\n1. Disable cron: `crontab -r` (backup first!)\n2. Identify problem: Check script logic\n3. Add rate limiting\n4. Restore with fix",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 385,
      "line_end": 390,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311348",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fb40ad51f6e8c0c2": {
      "id": "fb40ad51f6e8c0c2",
      "text": "### Resource Exhaustion\n1. Identify culprit: `ps aux --sort=-%mem`\n2. Kill problem processes\n3. Add resource limits\n4. Implement monitoring",
      "source": "skills/service-management/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 391,
      "line_end": 395,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311358",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7835528059a56cf5": {
      "id": "7835528059a56cf5",
      "text": "---\nname: perplexity-inspired\ndescription: Implements Perplexity AI-inspired features: query analysis, information synthesis, source citation, and current information priority.\nuser-invocable: true\n---\n\n# Perplexity-Inspired Skill\n\nImplements key features inspired by Perplexity AI's approach to information retrieval and synthesis.",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 10,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311404",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "075c62d0a590eddd": {
      "id": "075c62d0a590eddd",
      "text": "### 1. Query Analysis\n- Breaks down complex queries into searchable components\n- Identifies information needs and knowledge gaps\n- Determines optimal search strategies",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 13,
      "line_end": 17,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311415",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0248865f90b27e7d": {
      "id": "0248865f90b27e7d",
      "text": "### 2. Information Synthesis  \n- Combines information from multiple sources\n- Creates coherent, comprehensive responses\n- Identifies contradictions and consensus",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 18,
      "line_end": 22,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311426",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "41e2d2bfe8cb921b": {
      "id": "41e2d2bfe8cb921b",
      "text": "### 3. Source Citation\n- Tracks information sources\n- Provides citations for key facts\n- Evaluates source credibility",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 23,
      "line_end": 27,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311435",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7625ce30465bc3c5": {
      "id": "7625ce30465bc3c5",
      "text": "### 4. Current Information Priority\n- Flags outdated information\n- Prioritizes recent sources\n- Identifies time-sensitive queries",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 28,
      "line_end": 32,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311445",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b6706b3de32dfb4c": {
      "id": "b6706b3de32dfb4c",
      "text": "## Integration Points\n\n1. **Web Search**: When Brave API is configured, uses real-time web search\n2. **Memory System**: Integrates with OpenClaw memory for context\n3. **Source Database**: Maintains citation database for reference\n4. **Time Awareness**: Uses current date/time for recency evaluation",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 51,
      "line_end": 57,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311462",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d8baa2c715c4353b": {
      "id": "d8baa2c715c4353b",
      "text": "## Inspired By\n\nPerplexity AI's approach to:\n- Real-time web search integration\n- Source citation and transparency  \n- Current information prioritization\n- Query understanding and synthesis",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 58,
      "line_end": 65,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311474",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "25222f60577c88cb": {
      "id": "25222f60577c88cb",
      "text": "## Limitations\n\n- Web search requires Brave API key configuration\n- Source tracking depends on available metadata\n- Real-time updates limited by API access",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 66,
      "line_end": 71,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311485",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "250026d7739b5bd9": {
      "id": "250026d7739b5bd9",
      "text": "## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Multi-source aggregation**: Combine web, memory, and local knowledge\n2. **Credibility scoring**: Rate sources based on reliability\n3. **Trend detection**: Identify emerging topics and patterns\n4. **Query optimization**: Improve search strategy based on results",
      "source": "skills/perplexity-inspired/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 72,
      "line_end": 77,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311499",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b68ed333ed702523": {
      "id": "b68ed333ed702523",
      "text": "---\nname: acp-agent-protocol\ndescription: \"Agent Control Protocol (ACP) for OpenClaw - Connect to external AI agents like Claude Code, Codex, Pi, etc.\"\n---\n\n# ACP Agent Protocol Skill",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311546",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "2a22ec09177e0e7c": {
      "id": "2a22ec09177e0e7c",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nAgent Control Protocol (ACP) is OpenClaw's system for connecting to external AI agents for coding and specialized tasks. This skill provides guidance on setting up and using ACP with various AI providers.",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311558",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a476c4a8ba9bcf3a": {
      "id": "a476c4a8ba9bcf3a",
      "text": "## Current Status\n\n**⚠️ ACP Runtime Not Configured**\nError: `ACP runtime backend is not configured. Install and enable the acpx runtime plugin.`",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 12,
      "line_end": 16,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311570",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "539ca0cfd158e1ab": {
      "id": "539ca0cfd158e1ab",
      "text": "### 1. Install acpx Runtime Plugin",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 19,
      "line_end": 27,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311578",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f0c492eb767531ff": {
      "id": "f0c492eb767531ff",
      "text": "### 2. Configure ACP Providers\nACP supports various AI providers:\n- **Claude Code** (Anthropic)\n- **Codex** (OpenAI)\n- **Pi** (Inflection)\n- **Gemini** (Google)\n- Custom agents",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 28,
      "line_end": 35,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311590",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "883538a733075bd9": {
      "id": "883538a733075bd9",
      "text": "### 3. Set Up Agent Credentials\nEach provider requires API keys and configuration:",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 36,
      "line_end": 43,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311598",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a6f60cd81d200480": {
      "id": "a6f60cd81d200480",
      "text": "### Spawn ACP Sessions Programmatically",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 55,
      "line_end": 65,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311606",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6dbf1acae6b18fa1": {
      "id": "6dbf1acae6b18fa1",
      "text": "### Common ACP Agent IDs\n- `claude-code` - Anthropic's Claude for coding\n- `codex` - OpenAI Codex\n- `pi` - Inflection Pi\n- `gemini` - Google Gemini\n- Custom agent IDs configured in acp.providers",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 66,
      "line_end": 72,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311618",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "457c9b0fa968d92a": {
      "id": "457c9b0fa968d92a",
      "text": "### Gateway Configuration\nACP requires gateway configuration:",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 75,
      "line_end": 91,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311627",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8c1101306ffe546c": {
      "id": "8c1101306ffe546c",
      "text": "### Environment Variables",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 92,
      "line_end": 98,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311633",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6a3b8fcfe68a5d38": {
      "id": "6a3b8fcfe68a5d38",
      "text": "### Error: \"ACP runtime backend is not configured\"\n**Solution:** Install acpx runtime plugin",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 101,
      "line_end": 110,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311642",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "83635378e033dd44": {
      "id": "83635378e033dd44",
      "text": "### Error: \"agentId is not allowed\"\n**Solution:** Configure allowed agents in OpenClaw config",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 111,
      "line_end": 116,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311650",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b787d0a49210bc4a": {
      "id": "b787d0a49210bc4a",
      "text": "### Error: No ACP providers configured\n**Solution:** Set up at least one ACP provider",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 117,
      "line_end": 123,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311658",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d7ab0abb0c0b248e": {
      "id": "d7ab0abb0c0b248e",
      "text": "### 1. Simple Code Review",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 126,
      "line_end": 135,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311664",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c218ad0cf02222c1": {
      "id": "c218ad0cf02222c1",
