    },
    "809ca0e819ddc499": {
      "id": "809ca0e819ddc499",
      "text": "## Integration with Other Skills",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 158,
      "line_end": 159,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311683",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "45f1fffa0f8bf2fa": {
      "id": "45f1fffa0f8bf2fa",
      "text": "### With Coding-Agent Skill\nACP can complement the existing coding-agent skill:\n- **coding-agent**: Background processes, file exploration\n- **ACP**: Direct agent interaction, specialized coding tasks",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 160,
      "line_end": 164,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311705",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f9a93995614799ff": {
      "id": "f9a93995614799ff",
      "text": "### With Session Management\nACP sessions appear in `sessions_list()` and can be managed alongside subagent sessions.",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 165,
      "line_end": 167,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311715",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "2258ab79c01b465d": {
      "id": "2258ab79c01b465d",
      "text": "## Security Considerations\n\n1. **API Key Management**: Store keys securely, use environment variables\n2. **Session Isolation**: ACP sessions run isolated from main workspace\n3. **Cost Monitoring**: Track token usage for paid providers\n4. **Rate Limiting**: Configure appropriate rate limits for API calls",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 168,
      "line_end": 174,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311730",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "366f2e860a9ef4e2": {
      "id": "366f2e860a9ef4e2",
      "text": "## References\n\n- OpenClaw ACP Docs: `https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/acp`\n- Anthropic Claude API: `https://docs.anthropic.com`\n- OpenAI Codex: `https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/code`\n- OpenClaw GitHub: `https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw`",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 175,
      "line_end": 181,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311744",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "089c3aedfcf26866": {
      "id": "089c3aedfcf26866",
      "text": "## Next Steps\n\n1. Install acpx runtime plugin\n2. Configure at least one ACP provider (Claude Code recommended)\n3. Test with simple `openclaw acp client` command\n4. Integrate with existing workflow for coding tasks\n\n**Note:** ACP setup requires external API keys and may involve costs depending on the provider used.",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 182,
      "line_end": 189,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311760",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ecb9f8bde2232116": {
      "id": "ecb9f8bde2232116",
      "text": "# OpenClaw Integration Principle Skill\n\n**Core Principle**: Don't fight OpenClaw, work with it.",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 4,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311812",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8f8d1281db8a8270": {
      "id": "8f8d1281db8a8270",
      "text": "## Description\n\nWhen integrating external systems with OpenClaw, respect its architecture and constraints rather than trying to change them. Build bridges (services, adapters, wrappers) that OpenClaw can consume through its existing capabilities.",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 5,
      "line_end": 8,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311825",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e97ec9d640231d8b": {
      "id": "e97ec9d640231d8b",
      "text": "## When to Use This Skill\n\nUse this skill when:\n1. Integrating external AI models, APIs, or services with OpenClaw\n2. Facing compatibility issues between OpenClaw and external systems\n3. Designing new features that need to work with OpenClaw's architecture\n4. Encountering hardcoded constraints in OpenClaw that can't be changed\n5. Building sustainable, maintainable integration patterns",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 9,
      "line_end": 17,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311844",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7a6636b8bbdca2a8": {
      "id": "7a6636b8bbdca2a8",
      "text": "## The Fundamental Lesson",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 18,
      "line_end": 19,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311851",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fb55254ecfbab171": {
      "id": "fb55254ecfbab171",
      "text": "### ❌ The Wrong Approach (Fighting):",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 20,
      "line_end": 27,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311858",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "125928b58e97b37c": {
      "id": "125928b58e97b37c",
      "text": "### ✅ The Right Approach (Working With):",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 28,
      "line_end": 35,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311865",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "272bdbdf18f0aacd": {
      "id": "272bdbdf18f0aacd",
      "text": "## Real-World Example: E5 Embedding Integration",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 36,
      "line_end": 37,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311872",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "02d3a23e6f41ec04": {
      "id": "02d3a23e6f41ec04",
      "text": "### Problem:\n- **OpenClaw constraint**: 400+80 token chunks (hardcoded, not configurable)\n- **E5 limitation**: 512 token context window (model architecture)\n- **Incompatibility**: 480/512 = 94% capacity (insufficient buffer)",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 38,
      "line_end": 42,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311885",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "874306e7d7409cb2": {
      "id": "874306e7d7409cb2",
      "text": "### Failed Approach (Fighting):\n- Try to modify OpenClaw source code\n- Attempt to reconfigure chunk sizes (not possible)\n- Force E5 to accept larger inputs (impossible)\n- **Result**: \"Input is longer than the context size\" error",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 43,
      "line_end": 48,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311898",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1e6f4ff1482cc914": {
      "id": "1e6f4ff1482cc914",
      "text": "### Successful Approach (Working With):\n1. **Accept OpenClaw's HTTP provider capability** (existing feature)\n2. **Build E5 service with optimal 256+64 token chunks** (E5-compatible)\n3. **Let OpenClaw consume the service** (HTTP provider configuration)\n4. **Result**: Semantic search working through integration",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 49,
      "line_end": 54,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311914",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "52b3fdac3ab97fb6": {
      "id": "52b3fdac3ab97fb6",
      "text": "## Implementation Patterns",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 55,
      "line_end": 56,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311920",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f3b281210959189a": {
      "id": "f3b281210959189a",
      "text": "### 1. Service Bridges",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 57,
      "line_end": 62,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311926",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "88f21788dac9b7fb": {
      "id": "88f21788dac9b7fb",
      "text": "### 2. Adapter Layers",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 63,
      "line_end": 73,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311933",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f3cf1a74d8c2f679": {
      "id": "f3cf1a74d8c2f679",
      "text": "### 3. Configuration-Based Integration",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 74,
      "line_end": 84,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311939",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "5431a3226886bf16": {
      "id": "5431a3226886bf16",
      "text": "## Architectural Philosophy",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 85,
      "line_end": 86,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311945",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "145797aea8b9c420": {
      "id": "145797aea8b9c420",
      "text": "### 1. Respect System Boundaries\n- Each system has its own architecture and constraints\n- Trying to change fundamental constraints often fails\n- Better to understand and work within those constraints",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 87,
      "line_end": 91,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311957",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c97335266382308c": {
      "id": "c97335266382308c",
      "text": "### 2. Build Bridges, Not Modifications\n- **Bridges**: HTTP services, APIs, adapters, wrappers\n- **Modifications**: Source code changes, configuration hacks\n- **Prefer bridges**: More maintainable, less brittle",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 92,
      "line_end": 96,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311969",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "82140c82665c8121": {
      "id": "82140c82665c8121",
      "text": "### 3. Leverage Existing Capabilities\n- OpenClaw already has HTTP provider support\n- OpenClaw has configuration systems\n- OpenClaw has plugin/extensibility points\n- Connect existing capabilities instead of creating new ones",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 97,
      "line_end": 102,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311982",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "cb25a8f17eb3264f": {
      "id": "cb25a8f17eb3264f",
      "text": "### 4. User Experience First\n- End users shouldn't see the complexity\n- Integration should be transparent\n- Features should \"just work\" through OpenClaw",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 103,
      "line_end": 107,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.311993",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9e50b545b62768ae": {
      "id": "9e50b545b62768ae",
      "text": "### Before (Fighting Mindset):\n- \"Why won't OpenClaw let me configure X?\"\n- \"I need to fix OpenClaw's limitations\"\n- \"This should work if OpenClaw were different\"",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 110,
      "line_end": 114,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312004",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "de6a96bdbc9b7533": {
      "id": "de6a96bdbc9b7533",
      "text": "### After (Working With Mindset):\n- \"What capabilities does OpenClaw already have?\"\n- \"How can I build something OpenClaw can use?\"\n- \"How can I make these systems work together given their limitations?\"",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 115,
      "line_end": 119,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312016",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3c7459ba2148b775": {
      "id": "3c7459ba2148b775",
      "text": "## Practical Guidelines",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 120,
      "line_end": 121,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312022",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4380c82061dc7faf": {
      "id": "4380c82061dc7faf",
      "text": "### 1. Always Check First:\n- What OpenClaw capabilities already exist?\n- What configuration options are available?\n- What extension points are documented?",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 122,
      "line_end": 126,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312032",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "bda7a657d820a68d": {
      "id": "bda7a657d820a68d",
      "text": "### 2. Build Services, Not Hacks:\n- **Service**: Standalone component with clear API\n- **Hack**: Workaround that depends on internal details\n- **Prefer services**: More stable, easier to maintain",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 127,
      "line_end": 131,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312043",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b5acccdb241225b8": {
      "id": "b5acccdb241225b8",
      "text": "### 3. Test Integration Early:\n- Verify OpenClaw can consume your service\n- Test with real OpenClaw configuration\n- Validate end-to-end user experience",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 132,
      "line_end": 136,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312053",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7981b381068b515f": {
      "id": "7981b381068b515f",
      "text": "### 4. Document the Pattern:\n- How the integration works\n- Why this approach was chosen\n- How to maintain/extend it",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 137,
      "line_end": 141,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312063",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "19277da9a3851485": {
      "id": "19277da9a3851485",
      "text": "## Examples of This Principle in Action",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 142,
      "line_end": 143,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312069",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "2b160940c807d8ef": {
      "id": "2b160940c807d8ef",
      "text": "### E5 Semantic Search Integration\n- **Problem**: Context size incompatibility\n- **Solution**: HTTP service bridge\n- **Result**: Semantic search working through OpenClaw",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 144,
      "line_end": 148,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312079",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c53cf413b7890ae2": {
      "id": "c53cf413b7890ae2",
      "text": "### LangGraph Memory System\n- **Problem**: Missing dependencies in OpenClaw environment\n- **Solution**: External service with API\n- **Result**: Advanced memory features available to OpenClaw",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 149,
      "line_end": 153,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312091",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c1e85667d745c508": {
      "id": "c1e85667d745c508",
      "text": "### External Model Integration\n- **Problem**: OpenClaw doesn't support specific model API\n- **Solution**: Model proxy service\n- **Result**: Any model accessible through OpenClaw",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 154,
      "line_end": 158,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312102",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e7e041fa3c75a6b1": {
      "id": "e7e041fa3c75a6b1",
      "text": "## Common Pitfalls to Avoid",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 159,
      "line_end": 160,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312107",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "951af83df9f2ec68": {
      "id": "951af83df9f2ec68",
      "text": "### 1. Modifying OpenClaw Source\n- Breaks on updates\n- Hard to maintain\n- Risk of introducing bugs",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 161,
      "line_end": 165,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312116",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "22ae707a70eca259": {
      "id": "22ae707a70eca259",
      "text": "### 2. Assuming Configurability\n- Not all things are configurable\n- Hardcoded values exist for reasons\n- Test assumptions before building",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 166,
      "line_end": 170,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312125",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b41fe0e3a48e7296": {
      "id": "b41fe0e3a48e7296",
      "text": "### 3. Complex Workarounds\n- Simple solutions are more maintainable\n- Complexity increases failure points\n- KISS principle applies",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 171,
      "line_end": 175,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312135",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "182fe7ea257c0fb0": {
      "id": "182fe7ea257c0fb0",
      "text": "### 4. Ignoring OpenClaw Updates\n- Integration might break on updates\n- Stay aware of OpenClaw changes\n- Design for forward compatibility",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 176,
      "line_end": 180,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312144",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c9ffe05c3b0a995c": {
      "id": "c9ffe05c3b0a995c",
      "text": "## Integration Checklist\n\nBefore starting any OpenClaw integration:\n\n- [ ] **Identify OpenClaw capabilities** that can be used\n- [ ] **Understand constraints** that can't be changed\n- [ ] **Design service bridge** rather than modification\n- [ ] **Test with actual OpenClaw** configuration\n- [ ] **Document the pattern** for future reference\n- [ ] **Plan for maintenance** and updates",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 181,
      "line_end": 190,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312162",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "86788fdff064c925": {
      "id": "86788fdff064c925",
      "text": "## Related Skills\n\n- **http-service-bridge**: Creating HTTP services for OpenClaw integration\n- **configuration-management**: Working with OpenClaw configuration\n- **external-api-integration**: Connecting external APIs to OpenClaw\n- **model-adapter-pattern**: Adapting AI models for OpenClaw use",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 192,
      "line_end": 198,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312178",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4e921d5e83a7b224": {
      "id": "4e921d5e83a7b224",
      "text": "## Version History\n\n- **2026-03-03**: Created based on E5 integration experience\n- **Lesson learned**: Fighting OpenClaw constraints leads to failure; working with them leads to success",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 199,
      "line_end": 203,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312191",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ae4e9add56fc3bd9": {
      "id": "ae4e9add56fc3bd9",
      "text": "## Tags\n\n- integration\n- architecture\n- openclaw\n- best-practices\n- system-design\n- constraints\n- bridges\n- services",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 204,
      "line_end": 213,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312201",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "52dae9f86625968b": {
      "id": "52dae9f86625968b",
      "text": "---\n\n**Remember**: When OpenClaw says \"this is how I work,\" the answer is **\"OK, let me build something you can work with\"** not **\"let me force you to change.\"**",
      "source": "skills/openclaw-integration-principle/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 214,
      "line_end": 217,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312211",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9103bb9c7634e6a9": {
      "id": "9103bb9c7634e6a9",
      "text": "---\nname: audio-response\ndescription: \"Respond to audio messages with audio-only responses. Use when: (1) User sends audio message, (2) Protocol requires audio-only response, (3) Need to convert text to speech, (4) Label audio responses usefully.\"\n---\n\n# Audio Response Protocol",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312264",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ff907a38c6f29cd1": {
      "id": "ff907a38c6f29cd1",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nThis skill implements the audio-only response protocol: **When user inputs audio, respond with audio only.** It handles transcription, processing, TTS conversion, and labeled audio delivery.",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312276",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6e4dfdb327d7357f": {
      "id": "6e4dfdb327d7357f",
      "text": "### 1. **Input:** User sends audio message",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 14,
      "line_end": 14,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312283",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4a4605af648b6a70": {
      "id": "4a4605af648b6a70",
      "text": "### 2. **Processing:**\n   - Transcribe audio using Whisper\n   - Process the request\n   - Generate text response\n   - Convert to audio via TTS",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 15,
      "line_end": 19,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312293",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7fe106fb2d2dc963": {
      "id": "7fe106fb2d2dc963",
      "text": "### 3. **Output:** Send audio-only response with useful label",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 20,
      "line_end": 21,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312300",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "78c7f831a0cbdeb0": {
      "id": "78c7f831a0cbdeb0",
      "text": "## Labeling Format\n\nAudio responses are labeled with:\n\n**Examples:**\n- `[Disk Space] [15s] EBS volume solved capacity crisis`\n- `[Transcription] [8s] Whisper now working with 95% accuracy`\n- `[TTS Setup] [12s] espeak configured for basic audio responses`",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 22,
      "line_end": 33,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312315",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6bceabce58879a75": {
      "id": "6bceabce58879a75",
      "text": "### 1. **Local (espeak)** - Available now\n- **Pros:** No API, works offline, fast\n- **Cons:** Robotic voice, basic quality",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 36,
      "line_end": 42,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312325",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "51fd04ea06c3838e": {
      "id": "51fd04ea06c3838e",
      "text": "### 2. **OpenAI TTS** - Needs API key",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 43,
      "line_end": 53,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312332",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8a05de20bddbba91": {
      "id": "8a05de20bddbba91",
      "text": "### 3. **ElevenLabs** - Best quality",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 54,
      "line_end": 59,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312338",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ee8422ed86ac6f03": {
      "id": "ee8422ed86ac6f03",
      "text": "### 4. **Google TTS** - Free, requires internet",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 60,
      "line_end": 66,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312345",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e504e0677aa42ba1": {
      "id": "e504e0677aa42ba1",
      "text": "## Implementation Scripts",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 67,
      "line_end": 68,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312350",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c19725dac5a69b6e": {
      "id": "c19725dac5a69b6e",
      "text": "### `scripts/audio_responder.py`\nMain script that:\n1. Receives audio file path\n2. Transcribes using Whisper\n3. Generates response\n4. Converts to audio\n5. Sends with label",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 69,
      "line_end": 76,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312361",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0adb9a5c4ca5e34c": {
      "id": "0adb9a5c4ca5e34c",
      "text": "### `scripts/tts_engine.py`\nTTS conversion with fallback:\n1. Try ElevenLabs if configured\n2. Fall back to OpenAI TTS\n3. Fall back to Google TTS\n4. Final fallback: espeak",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 77,
      "line_end": 83,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312373",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "bfd5d74d036d9ae3": {
      "id": "bfd5d74d036d9ae3",
      "text": "### `scripts/label_generator.py`\nGenerate useful labels:\n- Extract topic from conversation\n- Estimate duration\n- Identify key point",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 84,
      "line_end": 89,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312383",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "83722df362cac46c": {
      "id": "83722df362cac46c",
      "text": "### Using espeak (immediate):",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 98,
      "line_end": 105,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312391",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a738b4f85909028d": {
      "id": "a738b4f85909028d",
      "text": "## Integration with OpenClaw",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 115,
      "line_end": 116,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312397",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "545281827b898f0d": {
      "id": "545281827b898f0d",
      "text": "### Telegram Handler:",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 117,
      "line_end": 133,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312404",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e95d04281240be2a": {
      "id": "e95d04281240be2a",
      "text": "### Auto-Configuration:\nScript checks and configures best available TTS:\n1. Check for ElevenLabs API key\n2. Check for OpenAI API key  \n3. Check for Google TTS (internet)\n4. Default to espeak",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 134,
      "line_end": 140,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312416",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "945acc2face56dcd": {
      "id": "945acc2face56dcd",
      "text": "## Label Generation Examples\n\n**Input:** \"How did you fix the disk space issue?\"\n**Output Label:** `[Infrastructure] [18s] Added 50GB EBS volume, now 47GB free`\n\n**Input:** \"Can you transcribe audio now?\"\n**Output Label:** `[Capabilities] [10s] Whisper transcription working with 9 files processed`\n\n**Input:** \"What's next?\"\n**Output Label:** `[Planning] [14s] Fix Moltbook cron, set up auto-transcription`",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 141,
      "line_end": 150,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312435",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a99961729e7fe366": {
      "id": "a99961729e7fe366",
      "text": "### TTS Failure:\n- Fall back to next available engine\n- If all fail, respond with text (breaking protocol, but informative)",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 154,
      "line_end": 157,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312445",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "328561ecbff5e12e": {
      "id": "328561ecbff5e12e",
      "text": "### Transcription Failure:\n- Use audio metadata (duration, format)\n- Generic response: \"Received your audio message\"",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 158,
      "line_end": 161,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312454",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c31b8c890f5d091a": {
      "id": "c31b8c890f5d091a",
      "text": "### Label Generation Failure:\n- Default label: `[Response] [{duration}s] Audio reply`",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 162,
      "line_end": 164,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312462",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f8f4856b72bcb99c": {
      "id": "f8f4856b72bcb99c",
      "text": "### Speed:\n- **espeak:** ~1x realtime (fastest)\n- **OpenAI TTS:** ~2-3s API call\n- **ElevenLabs:** ~3-5s API call\n- **Google TTS:** ~2-4s with internet",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 167,
      "line_end": 172,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312473",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "081e2a1f59ec82a6": {
      "id": "081e2a1f59ec82a6",
      "text": "### Quality:\n- **ElevenLabs:** Best (human-like)\n- **OpenAI TTS:** Very good\n- **Google TTS:** Good\n- **espeak:** Basic (robotic)",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 173,
      "line_end": 178,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312483",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b4b8991ed17616cb": {
      "id": "b4b8991ed17616cb",
      "text": "### Environment Variables:",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 181,
      "line_end": 187,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312490",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "72c2b839043fdb60": {
      "id": "72c2b839043fdb60",
      "text": "### Config File (`~/.config/audio-response.json`):",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 188,
      "line_end": 197,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312497",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e07b142467d7c675": {
      "id": "e07b142467d7c675",
      "text": "## Testing the Protocol\n\nSend an audio message to test:\n1. System transcribes it\n2. Processes request\n3. Generates audio response\n4. Sends with descriptive label\n\nThe first audio response will explain the TTS setup status.",
      "source": "skills/audio-response/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 198,
      "line_end": 206,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312510",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c7b2fd632646c706": {
      "id": "c7b2fd632646c706",
      "text": "---\nname: notion-browser-bridge\ndescription: \"Access Notion pages via browser automation when API access isn't available. Use when: (1) Notion page requires authentication but API integration is complex, (2) Need to read/write to Notion without OAuth setup, (3) Quick access to Notion content via browser control, (4) Notion's new API (post-2025-09-03) requires public OAuth integration which is overkill for internal use.\"\n---\n\n# Notion Browser Bridge",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312564",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "47beaa7dabfccbd5": {
      "id": "47beaa7dabfccbd5",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nThis skill enables browser-based access to Notion pages when API integration isn't practical. After Notion's September 2025 API changes, creating simple internal integrations with `secret_` tokens is no longer possible—all new integrations require public OAuth flow. This skill provides an alternative using OpenClaw's browser automation capabilities.",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312583",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ad02cd95cbd985e6": {
      "id": "ad02cd95cbd985e6",
      "text": "## When to Use This Approach\n\n**Use browser automation when:**\n- You need quick, one-time access to a Notion page\n- Setting up OAuth integration is overkill for your use case\n- The page is already accessible via browser (you're logged in)\n- You need to read content or make simple edits\n\n**Use Notion API when:**\n- You need programmatic, scalable access",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 12,
      "line_end": 21,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312602",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9efe8a068a220eec": {
      "id": "9efe8a068a220eec",
      "text": "- You can set up OAuth integration\n- You need to create/update databases programmatically\n- You're building a production integration",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 22,
      "line_end": 25,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312612",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6e3c2c4e9772bba6": {
      "id": "6e3c2c4e9772bba6",
      "text": "## Setup Requirements",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 26,
      "line_end": 27,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312618",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7fb533b3be96fbda": {
      "id": "7fb533b3be96fbda",
      "text": "### 1. Browser Configuration\n\nOpenClaw needs a browser profile with remote debugging enabled. The `brave-remote` profile works well:",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 28,
      "line_end": 46,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312629",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "76dc2239da04c4f2": {
      "id": "76dc2239da04c4f2",
      "text": "### 2. Start Browser with Remote Debugging\n\nLaunch Brave with remote debugging:\n\nOr use an existing browser instance that has remote debugging enabled.",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 47,
      "line_end": 55,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312639",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "bda19242dd942051": {
      "id": "bda19242dd942051",
      "text": "### 1. Connect to Notion Page",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 58,
      "line_end": 68,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312647",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "407d8dcbe4a58649": {
      "id": "407d8dcbe4a58649",
      "text": "### 2. Read Page Content",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 69,
      "line_end": 79,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312653",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e618f4f663dac6bb": {
      "id": "e618f4f663dac6bb",
      "text": "### 3. Interact with Elements",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 80,
      "line_end": 94,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312659",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "60d446112c863d3e": {
      "id": "60d446112c863d3e",
      "text": "### Pattern 1: Read Notion Table\n\nMany Notion pages use tables for project tracking. After taking a snapshot:\n\n1. Look for `table` elements in the snapshot\n2. Extract row and cell data from the structured output\n3. Map to your local project structure",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 97,
      "line_end": 104,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312674",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "96572338a541b377": {
      "id": "96572338a541b377",
      "text": "### Pattern 2: Navigate Linked Pages\n\nNotion pages often link to subpages. To access them:\n\n1. Find link elements in the snapshot (look for `link` refs)\n2. Click on the link using its ref\n3. Wait for navigation, then snapshot the new page",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 105,
      "line_end": 112,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312697",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "027ff5f1fd68d787": {
      "id": "027ff5f1fd68d787",
      "text": "### Pattern 3: Sync to Local Files\n\nCreate a sync workflow between Notion and local files (like PROJECT.md):\n\n1. Read Notion content via browser\n2. Parse and structure the data\n3. Update local markdown files\n4. Optionally: Push changes back to Notion by typing into editable fields",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 113,
      "line_end": 121,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312714",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "151e409bc2de8bcc": {
      "id": "151e409bc2de8bcc",
      "text": "### Issue: \"Profile not found\"\n**Solution:** Ensure the browser profile is configured in `openclaw.json` and the browser is running with remote debugging.",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 124,
      "line_end": 126,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312725",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6f47a4feed02ae35": {
      "id": "6f47a4feed02ae35",
      "text": "### Issue: \"Can't reach browser control service\"\n**Solution:** Check if the gateway is running (`openclaw gateway status`). Restart if needed.",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 127,
      "line_end": 129,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312734",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d3a8b59d9d2da853": {
      "id": "d3a8b59d9d2da853",
      "text": "### Issue: Notion page requires login\n**Solution:** Ensure you're already logged into Notion in the browser instance before automation.",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 130,
      "line_end": 132,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312744",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f904012e8840a728": {
      "id": "f904012e8840a728",
      "text": "### Issue: Elements not found in snapshot\n**Solution:** Use `refs: \"aria\"` in snapshot for more stable element references:",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 133,
      "line_end": 143,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312753",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "eece4eb5f4657711": {
      "id": "eece4eb5f4657711",
      "text": "## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Authentication:** The browser session uses your existing Notion login. Don't share the browser profile.\n2. **Rate limiting:** Notion may rate limit browser interactions. Add delays between actions.\n3. **Data privacy:** Only access pages you have permission to view.",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 144,
      "line_end": 149,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312768",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c0985e3106e1ffab": {
      "id": "c0985e3106e1ffab",
      "text": "## Example: MA Kooperation Page Sync\n\nToday's successful implementation:\n\n1. **Page:** `https://www.notion.so/MA-Kooperation-3165477ed88480cbbee8e7d1a91b50fe`\n2. **Content:** Project tracking table with deadlines, costs, bonuses\n3. **Structure:** Table → Rows → Cells with project details\n4. **Sync:** Extracted to PROJECT.md under \"Ghostwriting\" section",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 150,
      "line_end": 158,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312788",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "0f932dc9172d57ed": {
      "id": "0f932dc9172d57ed",
      "text": "## References\n\nSee `references/notion_patterns.md` for detailed element patterns and common Notion page structures.",
      "source": "skills/notion-browser-bridge/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 159,
      "line_end": 161,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312798",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ab990d6691198c12": {
      "id": "ab990d6691198c12",
      "text": "---\nname: audio-transcription-alt\ndescription: \"Alternative audio transcription methods that work within system restrictions. Use when: (1) Can't install Whisper system-wide, (2) Need lightweight solutions, (3) Quick transcription without full installation, (4) System has Python restrictions (PEP 668).\"\n---\n\n# Alternative Audio Transcription",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312860",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "db8c6cc6d656b5e8": {
      "id": "db8c6cc6d656b5e8",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nThis skill provides workarounds for audio transcription when system-wide Python installations are restricted (PEP 668). It includes methods that don't require `sudo` or breaking system packages.",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312873",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "5e2fd2f2f5bf23ae": {
      "id": "5e2fd2f2f5bf23ae",
      "text": "## The Problem: PEP 668 Restrictions\n\nModern Linux systems (Ubuntu 23.04+, Debian 12+) enforce PEP 668, which prevents `pip install` without `--break-system-packages` flag. This protects system integrity but makes installing tools like Whisper difficult.\n\n**Error message:**",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 12,
      "line_end": 20,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312888",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "684498d7969475e0": {
      "id": "684498d7969475e0",
      "text": "## Solution Approaches",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 21,
      "line_end": 22,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312894",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b208b37ada804f87": {
      "id": "b208b37ada804f87",
      "text": "### 1. Virtual Environments (Recommended)\nCreate isolated Python environments:",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 23,
      "line_end": 39,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312903",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7ba099dc2f6888c9": {
      "id": "7ba099dc2f6888c9",
      "text": "### 2. User Installation with `--user` Flag",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 40,
      "line_end": 48,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312911",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "bf803587a8a6f246": {
      "id": "bf803587a8a6f246",
      "text": "### 3. AppImage/Standalone Whisper\nUse pre-packaged Whisper binaries:",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 49,
      "line_end": 64,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312919",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c4dfe3238df801f9": {
      "id": "c4dfe3238df801f9",
      "text": "### 4. Docker Container\nRun Whisper in Docker:",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 65,
      "line_end": 76,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312927",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "88617ff767bc0785": {
      "id": "88617ff767bc0785",
      "text": "### 5. API Fallback\nWhen local installation isn't possible, use APIs:",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 77,
      "line_end": 90,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.312935",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "80d3ecad0dc916d3": {
      "id": "80d3ecad0dc916d3",
      "text": "## Scripts for Restricted Environments",
      "source": "skills/audio-transcription-alt/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 91,
      "line_end": 92,
