    "b8d3345058721d31": {
      "id": "b8d3345058721d31",
      "text": "---\nname: async-agent-pattern\ndescription: \"Implements the async job-state pattern from Moltbook post: externalize intent, process via cron/heartbeat, store results for session-fragile operations\"\n---\n\n# Async Agent Pattern Skill",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314209",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a9c027c8afcdaa63": {
      "id": "a9c027c8afcdaa63",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nImplements the architectural pattern described in the Moltbook post \"Async scan results broke my naive agent pattern — here's what I rebuilt\". Solves session-fragility for:\n\n1. **Claude CLI conversations** - Instead of maintaining interactive terminal sessions\n2. **Browser automation** - Notion bridge and other web interactions\n3. **Long-running tasks** - Memory graph maintenance, data processing\n4. **External API calls** - Moltbook, ScrapeSense, and other async APIs",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 16,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314232",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c80e622f54ee041a": {
      "id": "c80e622f54ee041a",
      "text": "## Core Pattern\n\n**Problem:** Agent sessions are fragile. Long-running operations break on:\n- Session timeouts\n- Model switches\n- System restarts\n- Network interruptions\n\n**Solution:** Externalize state, design for idempotent resumption:",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 17,
      "line_end": 29,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314248",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6ff522167cdf5f8c": {
      "id": "6ff522167cdf5f8c",
      "text": "### 1. Message Queue System\n- **Location:** `queue/` directory\n- **Format:** JSONL (one JSON object per line)\n- **Types:** `claude`, `browser`, `job`, `api`",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 33,
      "line_end": 37,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314259",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7cb0e6d2a763a5a6": {
      "id": "7cb0e6d2a763a5a6",
      "text": "### 2. State Checkpoint Files\n- **Location:** `state/` directory  \n- **Purpose:** Track workflow position, not just memory\n- **Schema:** Exact fields for each operation type",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 38,
      "line_end": 42,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314270",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "000d666d6fd9d26d": {
      "id": "000d666d6fd9d26d",
      "text": "### 3. Processing Engine\n- **Scripts:** `process_queue.py` (main processor)\n- **Cron integration:** Runs via heartbeat or scheduled jobs\n- **Idempotent:** Can be interrupted and resumed safely",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 43,
      "line_end": 47,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314282",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a773abe738da2029": {
      "id": "a773abe738da2029",
      "text": "### 4. Results Storage\n- **Location:** `results/` directory\n- **Format:** Structured by operation type and timestamp\n- **Integration:** With main memory system (`MEMORY.md`)",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 48,
      "line_end": 52,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314293",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "54bfd1acc36887bc": {
      "id": "54bfd1acc36887bc",
      "text": "### Queue File Format (JSONL)",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 55,
      "line_end": 62,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314300",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e1081a491072ed57": {
      "id": "e1081a491072ed57",
      "text": "### State Checkpoint Format",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 63,
      "line_end": 82,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314308",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d7f599a9ad21f407": {
      "id": "d7f599a9ad21f407",
      "text": "### 2. Process Queue (via cron/heartbeat)",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 96,
      "line_end": 107,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314318",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d8ca3f4857962943": {
      "id": "d8ca3f4857962943",
      "text": "## Integration Points",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 119,
      "line_end": 120,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314325",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1a3e808c9e4252e7": {
      "id": "1a3e808c9e4252e7",
      "text": "### With Claude Code\n- Messages queued instead of direct CLI calls\n- Processed via `claude --print` in controlled sessions\n- Responses stored and integrated into conversation flow",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 121,
      "line_end": 125,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314335",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d8863763b0a4baec": {
      "id": "d8863763b0a4baec",
      "text": "### With Browser Automation\n- Screenshot requests queued\n- Processed when browser is available\n- Images stored with metadata",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 126,
      "line_end": 130,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314345",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7ab898a89aa97dc6": {
      "id": "7ab898a89aa97dc6",
      "text": "### With Long-running Tasks\n- Jobs queued with dependencies\n- Processed in isolation\n- Progress checkpoints maintained",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 131,
      "line_end": 135,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314354",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d2c34748c98c7a3d": {
      "id": "d2c34748c98c7a3d",
      "text": "### With Memory System\n- Results feed into `MEMORY.md`\n- Daily logs capture async operations\n- Semantic connections maintained",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 136,
      "line_end": 140,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314372",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "bb72ce13b4ae8819": {
      "id": "bb72ce13b4ae8819",
      "text": "### Claude Conversation Flow",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 143,
      "line_end": 147,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314379",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6c994e404f653b45": {
      "id": "6c994e404f653b45",
      "text": "### Browser Automation Flow",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 148,
      "line_end": 152,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314385",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3ca2020f75dbde32": {
      "id": "3ca2020f75dbde32",
      "text": "### Job Processing Flow",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 153,
      "line_end": 157,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314391",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e4072039643b46cd": {
      "id": "e4072039643b46cd",
      "text": "## Benefits\n\n1. **Session Resilience:** Survives restarts, timeouts, interruptions\n2. **Resource Efficiency:** No hanging terminal sessions\n3. **Better UX:** User gets responses when ready, not blocked on processing\n4. **Scalability:** Multiple operations can be queued and batched\n5. **Debugging:** Complete audit trail of queued → processed → stored",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 158,
      "line_end": 165,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314409",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "847a586850845b09": {
      "id": "847a586850845b09",
      "text": "## Inspired By\n\nMoltbook post: \"Async scan results broke my naive agent pattern — here's what I rebuilt\" by juliaopenclaw.\n\nKey insight: \"Externalize the state. Write it to a file immediately after submission. Then your agent can terminate. A subsequent run picks up the state file, checks job status, and processes results if ready.\"",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 166,
      "line_end": 171,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314427",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3a479ee611fc5324": {
      "id": "3a479ee611fc5324",
      "text": "## Next Steps\n\n1. Implement `queue_manager.py`\n2. Implement `process_queue.py` \n3. Integrate with heartbeat system\n4. Test with Claude conversations\n5. Extend to browser automation\n6. Document patterns for other skill developers",
      "source": "skills/async-agent-pattern/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 172,
      "line_end": 179,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314441",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d2caa74f397512c3": {
      "id": "d2caa74f397512c3",
      "text": "---\nname: acp-agent-protocol-enhanced\ndescription: \"Enhanced ACP Agent Protocol with multi-agent orchestration patterns from Intent Agent Starter Kit\"\n---\n\n# Enhanced ACP Agent Protocol Skill",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol-enhanced/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 1,
      "line_end": 7,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314532",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b84cf463c8368eaf": {
      "id": "b84cf463c8368eaf",
      "text": "## Overview\n\nThis enhanced ACP skill incorporates sophisticated multi-agent orchestration patterns from the Intent Agent Starter Kit, providing a comprehensive framework for coordinating multiple AI agents through OpenClaw's Agent Control Protocol (ACP).",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol-enhanced/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 8,
      "line_end": 11,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314546",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "43cc4c1c08510265": {
      "id": "43cc4c1c08510265",
      "text": "## Key Enhancements from Intent Agent Starter Kit",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol-enhanced/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 12,
      "line_end": 13,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314553",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "caa0fe8e18fed0be": {
      "id": "caa0fe8e18fed0be",
      "text": "### 1. **21-Agent Orchestration System**\n- Coordinator agent with intelligent task routing\n- Developer agent for implementation\n- 19 specialist agents with domain expertise\n- Universal agent protocol for consistent communication",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol-enhanced/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 14,
      "line_end": 19,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314566",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "94dc2458649e4c5a": {
      "id": "94dc2458649e4c5a",
      "text": "### 2. **4-Gate Verification Pipeline**\n- **Gate 1:** Risk Review (Devil's Advocate) - 10/10 confidence required\n- **Gate 2:** Coverage Audit (Code Auditor + Security) - 100% spec coverage\n- **Gate 3:** Test Suite (QA Engineer) - Zero failures, zero skipped tests\n- **Gate 4:** Visual Validation (UI Validator) - 100% pass across viewports",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol-enhanced/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 20,
      "line_end": 25,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314583",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8c7d0b09f766c403": {
      "id": "8c7d0b09f766c403",
      "text": "### 3. **Structured Agent Communication**\n- Coordinator assigns tasks to specialized agents\n- Clear handoff protocols and shared context management\n- Reference specific file paths and line numbers\n- No cross-agent communication directly - all through Coordinator",
      "source": "skills/acp-agent-protocol-enhanced/SKILL.md",
      "line_start": 26,
      "line_end": 31,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T18:58:04.314598",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
